summary: An Ordinance granting to The Seattle Electric Company, its successors and assigns, a franchise to construct, maintain and operate a street railway upon certain parts of Rainier Avenue, Edmunds Street, Thirty-seventh Avenue South, Renton Avenue, Juneau Street, Thirty-ninth Avenue South, Holly Street, Forty-second Avenue South, Fifth Street, Waters Avenue, Avenue "L" and other streets, avenues and places in the City of Seattle.
